%% Diagram: Message broadcast — sender to global subscribers
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant CA as Client A (sender)
    participant ENV as Envoy edge
    participant WA as Webapp (PHP/Hack)
    participant DB as Vitess (MySQL)
    participant AS as Admin Server
    participant CS as Channel Server (owner)
    participant GR1 as Gateway (region R1)
    participant GR2 as Gateway (region R2)
    participant CB as Client B (R1)
    participant CC as Client C (R2)

    CA->>ENV: POST /chat.postMessage
    ENV->>WA: route to webapp
    WA->>DB: persist message
    DB-->>WA: ack
    WA->>AS: forward event (channel_id)
    AS->>AS: hash(channel_id) → owner CS
    AS->>CS: deliver event
    par broadcast to subscribed Gateways
        CS->>GR1: event for channel
        CS->>GR2: event for channel
    end
    par push to clients
        GR1->>CB: WebSocket push
        GR2->>CC: WebSocket push
    end
    Note over CA,CC: Target end-to-end: <500 ms globally
